text.section:
The provisions of subsection (1) of this section shall not apply to an inmate who:
Is not eligible for parole by statute;
Has been convicted of a capital offense or a Class A felony;
Has a maximum or close security classification as defined by administrative regulations promulgated by the department;
Has been sentenced to two (2) years or less of incarceration;
Is subject to the provisions of KRS 532.043; or
Has six (6) months or less to be served after his or her sentencing by a court or recommitment to prison for a violation of probation, shock probation, parole, or conditional discharge.
